name: flights-airport.csv
dataset_description: This dataset contains information about flights between various airports, represented by their IATA airport codes. It includes 5366 records detailing the number of flights from an origin airport to a destination airport. The dataset features two important categorical columns: 'origin' with 303 unique airport codes and 'destination' with 304 unique airport codes. The numerical column 'count' represents the number of flights, with values ranging from a minimum of 1 to a maximum of 13788 flights. The average number of flights is approximately 1306, with a standard deviation of 1593. The quartiles for the 'count' column are 293 (25th percentile), 777 (50th percentile), and 1718.5 (75th percentile). There are no date columns in this dataset.
